Title: Fast Lane for Confinement
Authors: Jiannis Pachos (MIT)
Comments: 17 pages, no figures, REVTEX
Report-no: MIT-CTP-2762
\\
  Within the Electric Schroedinger Representation of the Yang-Mills theory the
Hamiltonian eigenstate and eigenvalue, as well as the Coulomb and confining
potentials are presented for a special regularization-approximation scheme,
which focuses on the ultra-local behavior of the propagator.
